        "text": "\u201cAs we happen to be alone for the moment, and are both people of business,\u201d he said, when they had got back to the drawing-room and had sat down there in friendly relations, \u201clet me ask you--does the Doctor, in talking with Lucie, never refer to the shoemaking time, yet?\u201d  \u201cNever.\u201d",
